123.8	Sikhism	Sikhism	Sikhismnote 1 ( or ; Punjabi: , , IPA: ) is a monotheistic religion founded during the 15th century in the Punjab region, by Guru Nanak Dev and continued to progress with ten successive Sikh gurus (the last teaching being the holy scripture Gurū Granth Sāhib Ji). It is the fifth-largest organized religion in the world, with over 30 million Sikhs and one of the most steadily growing. This system of religious philosophy and expression has been traditionally known as the Gurmat (literally 'of the gurus'). Punjab of India is the only region in the world with a majority Sikh population.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/06/Amritsar-golden-temple-00.JPG/220px-Amritsar-golden-temple-00.JPG
